It seems it is not ok. There are still failing tests in travis (for example RequiredActionTotpSetupTest) and I think that the reason is exactly this.
The execution doesn't necessarily need to have "flowId" filled. The AuthenticationExecutions, which point to the Authenticator implementations, don't have the "flowId" filled at all. I think you can just return from the method in case that checkFlow doesn't exists. Maybe something like this:
            if (checkFlow == null) {
                return;
            }

